[
  {
    "text": "Hello, and welcome to Advance Scene Understanding in AR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this video I'll introduce the new capabilities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "of ARKit and RealityKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=7"
  },
  {
    "text": "enabled by the LiDAR Scanner on the new iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "iOS and ipadOS provide developers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "with two powerful frameworks to help you build apps for AR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "ARKit combines positional tracking, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "scene understanding, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "and integration with rendering technologies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable a variety of AR experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "using either the back-facing or front-facing camera.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "And RealityKit -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "a new high-level framework built specifically for AR -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "provides photorealistic rendering and special effects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=37"
  },
  {
    "text": "scalable performance, and a Swift-based API, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=40"
  },
  {
    "text": "making it easy to prototype and build great AR experiences.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today we're excited to talk about advances ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "in both frameworks, which are only made possible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=50"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the hardware capabilities on the new iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new iPad Pro comes equipped with a LiDAR Scanner.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is used to determine distance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "by measuring at nanosecond speeds ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "how long it takes for light to reach an object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "in front of you and reflect back.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is effective up to five meters away ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=70"
  },
  {
    "text": "and operates both indoors and outdoors.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "And coupling this capability with information captured ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=76"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the Wide and Ultra Wide cameras gives you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=79"
  },
  {
    "text": "an incredible understanding of your environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's see how this improves AR experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "built with each of these frameworks, starting with ARKit.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=88"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new update to ARKit version 3.5 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "delivers a number of new features and improvements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=95"
  },
  {
    "text": "that take full advantage of the LiDAR Scanner ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the new iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scene Geometry is a new API that provides your apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=102"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a detailed topological map of your surrounding environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "The LiDAR Scanner also simplifies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "the AR onboarding experience by more quickly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "and more accurately detecting surfaces.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "And existing ARKit features -- including motion capture, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=118"
  },
  {
    "text": "people occlusion, and raycasting -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "also benefit without requiring ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "any additional application changes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's start with Scene Geometry.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=128"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scene Geometry provides you with a triangle mesh, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "representing a topological mapping of your environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "And optionally, that mesh can include semantic information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "that classifies what's being seen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "This includes things like tables and chairs, floors, walls, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "ceilings, the windows, and so on.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "All this information could be used to allow occlusion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "of virtual content by real-world objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "environment-dependent physics, and illumination of both real ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "and virtual objects in your scene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's see this mapping in action.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=162"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's an example being taken from an indoor scene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=166"
  },
  {
    "text": "We're overlaying the AR frame image with a mesh ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "being generated by ARKit, using the LiDAR sensor.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can see as we sweep around the room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "how quickly we're able to detect the shape of the furniture ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the layout of the environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "And the colors are based on a classification ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "of what the mesh overlays.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's take a look at the API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scene Geometry is enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "through a new scene reconstruction property ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "on ARWorldTtrackingConfiguration.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, there's two options, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "depending on what data you'd like to have generated.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first option is to generate just the mesh, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning only the topological information will be surfaced.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is intended for apps doing things like object placement, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "where they don't depend on a classification ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the surrounding objects.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "The other option is .meshWithClassification.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "And as the name implies, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "this adds semantic classification ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "for all the Scene Geometry.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is helpful for apps that want different behaviors, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "depending on what's in the scene, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as different lighting on the floor ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "versus on the table.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "And here down below, you see the code; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=233"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's pretty simple.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=235"
  },
  {
    "text": "We're using world tracking, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "and we test to verify that we're running on a device ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=237"
  },
  {
    "text": "that supports scene reconstruction.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "If so, then we select the mesh option here ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "and start running the session.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once the session is running with scene reconstruction enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=247"
  },
  {
    "text": "the AR session will return AR mesh anchors.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "These are just like any other anchor, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "and changes come through the usual ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "AR session delegate methods, like did add(anchor:), ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "did update(anchor:), and did remove(anchor:).",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=259"
  },
  {
    "text": "And each mesh anchor represents a local area of mesh geometry.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's described with a transform of the anchor ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "and a mesh geometry object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "An ARMeshGeometry object holds all the information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you'll need to represent the surrounding environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "Each object contains a list of vertices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "normals, faces, and a semantic classification ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "if enabled for each phase.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "These are all provided as MTLBuffers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=285"
  },
  {
    "text": "to allow them to be directly integrated into your renderers.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now there's some interesting interplay that happens ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "between Scene Geometry and plane detection.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=294"
  },
  {
    "text": "When scene reconstruction and plane detection ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "are both enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "the mesh that's constructed will be flattened ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=300"
  },
  {
    "text": "to match overlapping planes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is useful for an object placement ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "where surfaces need to be consistently flat ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=306"
  },
  {
    "text": "to allow for a smooth object movement.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=309"
  },
  {
    "text": "On the other hand, if you're using Scene Geometry, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "and plane detection is not enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "the mesh will no longer be flattened.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "But this combination ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "will preserve more detail in the meshed surfaces.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, so that's Scene Geometry.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "Moving on, there's several more improvements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "enabled by the LiDAR Scanner.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first is much simpler and faster onboarding.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "With the LiDAR Scanner, planer surfaces are detected ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "almost instantly and more accurately as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is true even on low-features surfaces, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "like white walls.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=342"
  },
  {
    "text": "So the result is that the plane-detection onboarding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "that previously took a few seconds ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "and required some amount of user guidance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "can now occur completely seamlessly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "And no changes are necessary.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=353"
  },
  {
    "text": "All ARKit apps will benefit from this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "when running on the new iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "Existing apps will also benefit from improved raycasting.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "The enhanced scene understanding of ARKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "allows quicker and more accurate raycasting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "against horizontal and vertical planes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=369"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, the new iPad Pro can raycast ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "against a wider range of surfaces than ever before.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "Just set the allowing target to estimatedPlane ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "and data from the LiDAR Scanner will provide raycasting results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "that match the surrounding environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, objects can now be placed on all surfaces ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "of a large chair or a couch as seen here.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=391"
  },
  {
    "text": "Motion Capture and people occlusion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "are also improved due to the LiDAR Scanner ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "providing more accurate depth information.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=398"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apps using Motion Capture will benefit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=401"
  },
  {
    "text": "from a more accurate scale estimation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the depth values for people occlusion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=405"
  },
  {
    "text": "are more accurate as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "In addition, people occlusion and the Scene Geometry API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "can work together when both features are enabled.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "The very dynamic geometry of people ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be excluded from the scene reconstruction, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "which in turn, provides a more stable mesh ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the real-world environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=423"
  },
  {
    "text": "So that's a quick look at ARKit 3.5 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the new iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scene Geometry provides a topological map ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=430"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the environment around you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "Planer surfaces are detected almost instantly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=434"
  },
  {
    "text": "and more accurately, which simplifies onboarding.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "Raycasting is more accurate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "and can take Scene Geometry into account, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "and Motion Capture and people occlusion are improved as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "ARKit is also tightly integrated ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=449"
  },
  {
    "text": "with our higher-level AR framework called RealityKit.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=451"
  },
  {
    "text": "RealityKit provides photo-realistic rendering, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "camera effects, animations, physics, and a lot more.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "It was built from the ground up specifically for AR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "RealityKit takes advantage of the new ARKit 3.5 features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "and makes it really easy for you to integrate them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "into either new or existing RealityKit apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "These capabilities can be accessed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=476"
  },
  {
    "text": "through the new scene understanding API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "It provides options for enabling LiDAR-enhanced physics, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "occlusion, and lighting, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's all access through some simple settings on the ARView, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "so let's take a look.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "With the new iPad Pro, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "RealityKit is able to determine physics interactions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "between virtual objects in the Scene Geometry ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "from surfaces we detect in the real world.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "So you can have a virtual ball ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=502"
  },
  {
    "text": "bounce off of your real-world furniture.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=503"
  },
  {
    "text": "To do this, first you'll generate collision shapes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=506"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your virtual content, the ModelEntity, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=508"
  },
  {
    "text": "and initialize its physics body.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=511"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then just add the physics option ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your ARView's sceneUnderstanding.options set, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "and RealityKit will take care of the rest.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "Likewise with occlusion, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "RealityKit uses the Scene Geometry ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "that's detected from real-world objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=525"
  },
  {
    "text": "like doorways, and tables, chairs, and so on ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=527"
  },
  {
    "text": "to occlude the virtual objects in your scene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=530"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is totally automatic.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=533"
  },
  {
    "text": "All it takes to enable this is to add occlusion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=535"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the sceneUnderstanding.options set ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your ARView.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=539"
  },
  {
    "text": "RealityKit will take care of everything else under the hood, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "and your virtual content will be occluded ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=543"
  },
  {
    "text": "by all the major objects in the environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's an example of that.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=548"
  },
  {
    "text": "Our virtual robot is walking around on the floor.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "But you'll see as the camera moves behind the column, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=553"
  },
  {
    "text": "the robot is occluded.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=556"
  },
  {
    "text": "Its geometry is disappearing from the rendering, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that helps maintain the illusion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=560"
  },
  {
    "text": "of proper depth in the scene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=562"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now the third piece is for lighting.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "With a new RealityKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=568"
  },
  {
    "text": "your virtual light sources can illuminate real-world surfaces.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=570"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is because we're able to illuminate the Scene Geometry, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=574"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is very accurately fitted to those surfaces ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=577"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the help of the LiDAR Scanner.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=580"
  },
  {
    "text": "And like before, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "enabling this is just as simple as adding receivesLighting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=583"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the ARView's sceneUnderstanding.options set.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=586"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, support for these features extends to scenes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=589"
  },
  {
    "text": "built in Reality Composer as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "Physics can be configured to collide virtual objects ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the real world using the Scene Geometry mesh, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=597"
  },
  {
    "text": "and occlusion of virtual content by real-world objects ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=600"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be enabled in the Inspector panel.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=603"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information, please visit developer.apple.com ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=606"
  },
  {
    "text": "where you'll find links to documentation, sample code, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=610"
  },
  {
    "text": "or developer videos like this one, and a lot more.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=613"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you for watching!",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-609/?time=616"
  }
]